About Me

Recently, I completed my Bachelor's degree in Computing Science at Griffith College Dublin. Over the past 4 years, I have acquired extensive knowledge in various programming areas. For my final Software Development Project in Griffith College I developed the video game called Red Depths Of North Pole about underwater soviet sci-fi station, which player has to explore as a professional soldier. Computing Science course teachers were impresed by my video game and invited me to Creative Showcase Exhibition 2024 where I proudly presented Red Depths Of North Pole project GriffithCreativeShow-2024

I'm a passionate gamer and movie enthusiast with my own YouTube channel where I discuss video games and movies. I create scripts, edit videos using Adobe Premiere Pro and Adobe Photoshop, and have a powerful laptop for my work.

During my studies, I consistently completed all projects on time and maintained high attendance in lectures. I also gained experience in teamwork through various group projects, establishing myself as a reliable team player.
